Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Huge Floor to Ceiling Glass Shopfronts

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Forum, located above St Leonards Train Station and adjacent to the main bus stop to North Sydney and Sydney's CBD, is a major retail hub servicing residents, office workers, commuters and hospital staff.

Current retailers include IGA, McDonald's, KFC, Oporto, Priceline, BWS, Baker's Delight, Groomsmen plus an abundance of food & beverage operators.

* Retail spaces on offer: 42sqm*, 48sqm & 101sqm*
* Option for internal facing tenancies or have exposure along Pacific Highway or Sergeants Lane
* Recently upgraded, shared external seating areas
* Huge floor to ceiling glass shopfronts
* Excellent passing trade with 10.4million passenger movements per annum*
* Surrounded by St Leonards CBD with approximately 300,000sqm* of net lettable office space and directly under 782 residential apartments
* Huge demand for coffee, food & beverage (not heavy cooking), retail and services
* Main transport hub for medical workers going to and from both Royal North Shore public and private hospitals

For further details, or to arrange an inspection, please contact Amy Pfeiffer 0401 198 401.

*approximate
** Source: 2016 Opal Data from NSW Government, B&P Research, Observation and Analysis
